commit.message:
Compile the --enable-gtk3 option with -Wno-deprecated-declarations

This is a GTK+ 2 application ported to GTK+ 3, not a native GTK+ 3
application. The deprecated GTK+ 3 features will most likely not be
removed and can still be used.

Add this compiler option so that only really important warnings are
issued.

Fix configuring with --enable-man

It is not always possible to force regeneration of the man page after
commit c87d4e5e7f5e84c44ee594eccd43c6618195f017.

Check the prerequisites to regenerate the man page during configuration
instead of reporting an error later during the build process, and remove
the pre-generated man page after checking, so that --enable-man will
regenerate the man page no matter what.

Re-enable compiling with vte-2.90

GdkColor has no member named 'alpha'.

This fixes a regression introduced in
commit a7a7162206e1f0375a92f39facdea883b68dec4c,
github pull request #100.
Adjust the vte versions necessary for compiling

Enable installation with configure defaults

The configure default for the man page without DocBook installed is
to not generate it. However, this default results in an error during
installation.

Add a pre-generated man page and make the xsltproc command do nothing
in this case.

commit.message:
fix: Fix VTE background echoes

This workaround is found in vte/src/app/app.cc, that avoiding letting
window painting the background can avoid background echoes.  However this
will cause other elements in the terminal window to have their background
transparent if not set.  To workaround this, we have to add background
color to the vbox of the window.
